  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What should I search in Quora?",
  "response": "When using Quora, your searches should align with your interests, goals, or curiosities. Here\u2019s a structured guide to help you explore effectively:\n\n### 1. **Personal Experiences**  \n   - **Examples**:  \n     - \"What\u2019s it like to work at Google?\"  \n     - \"How did you overcome failure?\"  \n   - Great for learning from others\u2019 life stories or challenges.\n\n### 2. **Expert Advice**  \n   - **Examples**:  \n     - \"Career tips from a software engineer\"  \n     - \"Medical perspectives on intermittent fasting\"  \n   - Look for answers from professionals or verified experts.\n\n### 3. **Specific Topics**  \n   - **Examples**:  \n     - \"Climate change impacts on agriculture\"  \n     - \"Blockchain technology explained simply\"  \n   - Dive deep into academic, technical, or niche subjects.\n\n### 4. **How-To Guides**  \n   - **Examples**:  \n     - \"How to start a podcast in 2024?\"  \n     - \"Steps to learn Python for beginners\"  \n   - Practical, step-by-step advice for skills or projects.\n\n### 5. **Recommendations**  \n   - **Examples**:  \n     - \"Best books on entrepreneurship\"  \n     - \"Affordable skincare routines for dry skin\"  \n   - Crowdsourced suggestions for products, services, or resources.\n\n### 6. **Current Events & Debates**  \n   - **Examples**:  \n     - \"Pros and cons of remote work\"  \n     - \"Analysis of the 2024 election trends\"  \n   - Explore diverse viewpoints on trending issues.\n\n### 7. **Niche Interests**  \n   - **Examples**:  \n     - \"History of medieval swordfighting\"  \n     - \"Birdwatching tips in urban areas\"  \n   - Quora\u2019s community often covers obscure or specialized topics.\n\n### 8. **Career & Education**  \n   - **Examples**:  \n     - \"MBA vs. self-taught business skills\"  \n     - \"How to transition into data science?\"  \n   - Guidance on resumes, degrees, or industry shifts.\n\n### 9. **Entertainment & Pop Culture**  \n   - **Examples**:  \n     - \"Theories about the *Stranger Things* finale\"  \n     - \"Underrated 90s movies\"  \n   - Discussions on movies, TV, music, or celebrities.\n\n### 10. **Self-Improvement**  \n    - **Examples**:  \n      - \"How to build confidence?\"  \n      - \"Morning routines of successful people\"  \n    - Tips for mental health, productivity, or habits.\n\n### **Pro Tips**:  \n- **Use Keywords**: Be specific (e.g., \"Python for data analysis\" vs. \"coding\").  \n- **Follow Topics/Spaces**: Tailor your feed by following hashtags or communities (e.g., Space for \"Startup Founders\").  \n- **Trending Sections**: Check Quora\u2019s trending topics for popular discussions.  \n- **Engage**: Ask questions or answer others to build connections.  \n\nQuora\u2019s strength lies in its diverse user base\u2014combine curiosity with targeted searches to get the most value! \ud83c\udf1f",
